                <div>
                  <strong>Engineering review</strong>
                  <span>XFPCB CAM team reviews stackup, impedance targets, DFM rules, and material compatibility. Report delivered within 4&ndash;24 hours.</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="f4-cp-step">
                <span class="f4-cp-num">3</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Quotation and consultation summary</strong>
                  <span>Structured quotation with recommended stackup, impedance verification plan, lead time options, and cost breakdown by quantity tier.</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="f4-cp-step">
                <span class="f4-cp-num">4</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Production and verification</strong>
                  <span>Impedance coupons on every panel, TDR verification recorded, DFM-checked fabrication, electrical test, visual inspection, export packing.</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="f4-consult-checklist">
              <h4>To include for a complete engineering review:</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Gerber files (RS-274X) with all copper, soldermask, silkscreen, and outline layers</li>
                <li>NC drill file with tool list and drill symbol definitions</li>
                <li>Stackup diagram or specification (target board thickness, layer purpose, dielectric type)</li>
